        public String toString(int f)
        Return a String representation of this FloatEvent using a timestamp with the specified fractional second precision displayed. Note: using a value of 6 (microseconds) is generally the max precision (A precision up to 9, nanoseconds, is supported, but rounding errors prevent proper conversion).
